actions.
This period of transition becomes extremely difficult for many young Black males because they not only must accomplish the developmental tasks that come with the adolescent period but must also grapple with many of the negative socioeconomic pressures that are a part of their reality. During this period the young Black male is experiencing extreme stress and strain as he searches for relief, sometimes via drugs, from the daily pressures of everyday living.
